    <!-- #94: shown when the device's charge counter is too inaccurate to trust the capacity/health reading.
         Shared by the home Capacity row ("Unknown" + info icon) and the insights health figure (warning icon). -->
    <string name="battery_reading_unreliable_cd">Why this battery reading may be unreliable</string>
    <string name="battery_reading_unreliable_dialog_title">Battery reading may be unreliable</string>
    <string name="battery_reading_unreliable_dialog_message" formatted="false">This device reports a full-charge capacity that doesn\'t match the rated capacity you entered, so the measured capacity — and the health figure based on it — can\'t be trusted here.\n\nThis is usually a quirk of the phone\'s battery hardware (some chipsets report the charge counter incorrectly), not a problem with your battery.\n\nBut it can also mean the battery is genuinely wearing out. Watch for these signs:\n\n• The phone shuts down or restarts under heavy load even though it still shows charge left\n• The level collapses near the bottom (e.g. 20% behaves like 2%)\n• It drains much faster than it used to\n\nIf you notice these, consider having the battery replaced.</string>

